condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Deposit of Recipient's funds | Description :The Recipient shall deposit into the Project Account the amountindicated in the Annual Work Plan and Budget to be provided by the Recipient for the financing of the Project Implementing Entity'soperation and other Project related activities for the next quarter(“Counterpart Funds”). | Frequency :Quarterly

Finance Agreement :Draft Annual work plan | Description :The Recipient shall prepare, shall cause the Project Implementing Entityto prepare and furnish to the Recipient, and shall submit to the Steering Committee and then to IDA for approval, a draft annualwork plan (including Training and Operating Costs), and budget (including Counterpart Funds) for the Project, of such scope anddetail as the Association shall have reasonably requested. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Draft Budget Law | Description :The Recipient shall provide to IDA evidence, in form and substance satisfactoryto the Association that the draft budget law including the Recipient's annual budget for the next fiscal year submitted to theRecipient's parliament for enactment reflects a proposalto increase the annual resources for the Project Implementing Entity'soperations in an amount satisfactory to IDA. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Environmental Audits, Strategic Environmental and Social Assessment | Description :The Recipient shall furnishto IDA the Environmental Audits, as well as the Strategic Environmental and Social Assessment, each in form and substanceacceptable to the Association. | Due Date :31-Dec-2013

Finance Agreement :Establishment of the Project Implementing Entity (PIE) | Description :The Project Implementing Entity has beenestablished in accordance with Section I.A.4 of Schedule 2 of the Financing Agreement. | Due Date :30-Nov-2012

Finance Agreement :Independent Auditor - Environmental Audits | Description :The Recipient shall recruit an independent auditor onthe basis of terms of reference, qualifications and experience satisfactory to the Association (IDA) for the purpose of carryingoutthe Environmental Audits. | Due Date :30-Apr-2013

Finance Agreement :Matching Grant Agreement | Description :A Matching Grant Agreement has been entered into between the PIE and theBeneficiary in accordance with Section I.D.2 of Schedule 2to the Financing Agreement. | Due Date :31-Mar-2014

Finance Agreement :Mid Term Review | Description :The Recipient shall, in conjunction with the Association and the ProjectImplementing Entity, carry out a mid-term review of the Project (the “Mid-term Review”), covering the progress achieved in theimplementation of the Project. | Due Date :22-Oct-2015

Finance Agreement :Project Account | Description :The Recipient has opened a Project Account in accordance with Section I.G.2 (a)of Schedule 2 to the Financing Agreement, and made an initial deposit of not less than one fourth of the amount indicated in theAnnual Work Plan and Budget for the year during which the first disbursement is made, as Counterpart Funds, in the Project Account| Due Date :31-Dec-2012
Finance Agreement :Recruitment of Independent Auditors | Description :The Recipient and the PIE shall engage independent auditors.| Due Date :31-Jan-2014

Finance Agreement :Recruitment of PIE specific staff | Description :The PIE has recruited in accordance with the provisions ofSection III of Schedule 2 to the Financing Agreement, the following staff each with terms of reference, qualifications andexperience satisfactory to IDA, for the purpose of working at least part time specifically on the activities carried out by thePIE, under the Project: a financial management specialist and a procurement specialist. | Due Date :31-Mar-2013

Finance Agreement :Signing of the Project Agreement | Description :The Project Agreement has been signed by the ProjectImplementing Entity and a legal opinion in form and substance satisfactory to IDA, issued by legal counsel acceptable to IDA forthe purpose of issuing legal opinions under the laws of the Recipient, has confirmed that the Project Agreement is valid, bindingand enforceable in accordance with its terms under the laws of the Recipient. | Due Date :31-Jan-2013

Finance Agreement :Signing of the Subsidiary Agreement | Description :The Subsidiary Agreement has been signed by the Recipient andthe PIE and a legal opinion in form and substance satisfactory to IDA, issued by legal counsel acceptable to IDA for the purpose ofissuing legal opinions under the laws of the Recipient, has confirmedthat the Subsidiary Agreement is valid, binding andenforceable in accordance with its terms under the laws of the Recipient. | Due Date :28-Feb-2013

Finance Agreement :Update of the Project Implementation Manual (PIM) | Description :The Project Implementation Manual has beenupdated as needed to include guidelines, principles and procedures applicable for the implementation of Part 1(c)(iv) of theProject. | Due Date :31-Jan-2014
